The "ICD Title" is the term for any ICD concept (unit, entity or category) which labels the intended concept in a meaningful, unambiguous way

The "Fully Specified Name" is a term that describes the entity in a clear and understandable way and usually contains more details than the "ICD Title". THIS FIELD MAY BE LEFT EMPTY. In that case the "ICD Title" will be used also as the "Fully Specified Name"

Base Index Terms indicate language terms that may correspond with ICD entities and consist of Synonyms and Narrower Terms. Some of these base index terms may be used also as base inclusion terms (please mark them, if it is the case).
Check this if the term is deprecated (i.e. not to be used in the future).

Inclusion terms are either index terms (i.e. synonyms or narrower terms) OR foundation component subclasses that are not part of a classification hierarchy. Please choose here the base inclusion terms from descendants, i.e. subclasses that should be listed as inclusions, in case they are not included in a particular linearization.

Exclusion terms help users eliminate entities that should be assigned to a different ICD category because of differences in meaning or terminology. Base exclusion terms are independent of linearizations, and are used during the linearization process to create the exclusions of a category.
